list.abstract: UNTIL（英[ənˈtɪl]，美[ənˈtɪl]），英文单词，词性是介词，释义为直到…时；到…为止。短语搭配有not ... until ...（直到...才）。例句有“He didn't fall asleep until midnight.（他直到半夜才睡着。）” UNTIL连词类近义词有before、介词有by the end、ere。until常与not连用，表示“直到...才...”，注意not的翻译。
Until是C语言里的术语之一，不过不常用。大多数情况下由do while代替。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, I, I just want to... Look, have you lived across from someone your whole life, but you don't really appreciate them until...
yingyinNormal.zh: 我只是想……你有没有这辈子都住在某个动物的对面，但是之前从来没好好注意过她，直到……

yingyinNormal.en: He waited until the last minute.
yingyinNormal.zh: 可是他等到最后一刻才来。

yingyinNormal.en: It won't come until it's called.
yingyinNormal.zh: 它受到召唤才会出现。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets》

yingyinNormal.en: Cary, we don't decide until we vote.
yingyinNormal.zh: 凯里，我们投票之后才能决定。

yingyinNormal.en: That is, until I saw my first sign of life.
yingyinNormal.zh: 直到我第一次亲眼目睹生命的迹象。

yingyinNormal.en: Lizzie, we shall have no peace until she goes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 伊丽莎白，如果丽迪雅不走，我们永无安宁的生活。

yingyinNormal.en: How long until they announce the numbers, Mommy?
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们还有多久才会公布号码呢，妈咪？

yingyinNormal.en: Nothing will happen until we have proof of life.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不证明他们还活着，我们什么都不做。

yingyinNormal.en: We progress forward until we encounter setbacks.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们前进时会遇到挫折。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm not leaving here until we have an agreement.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不达成协议，我不会离开这里的。

yingyinNormal.en: We wandered the sewers until I found this place.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们在下水道里游荡，直到我们发现了这里。

yingyinNormal.en: Until 18 months from now, when you are replaced.
yingyinNormal.zh: 直到18个月之后，你下台。

yingyinNormal.en: Jay, they delayed Sonia's flight until tomorrow.
yingyinNormal.zh: 杰，桑娅的航班延误到了明天。

yingyinNormal.en: How long until your employers decide to kill you?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你上司什么时候决定把你除掉？

yingyinNormal.en: Containment? Until there is a better option, yes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 只是遏制？直到有一个更好的选择，是吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Until ten years from now when you're still single.
yingyinNormal.zh: 等十年后你还是单身狗，你就有兴趣了。

yingyinNormal.en: Fine. You're staying with us until we find a cave.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好，我们找到山洞之前你跟我们呆在一起。

yingyinNormal.en: I should hold the money for you until you're older.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以在你长大之前，就由我来替你保管这笔钱吧。

yingyinNormal.en: Whatever happened to "don't speak until spoken to"?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你不说话，没人当你是哑巴？

yingyinNormal.en: Yes, it has been very pleasant until now. Gentlemen.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是啊，是挺开心的，在见到你之前，先生们。

word_level_phrase_info.brief_definition: 直到现在；直至现在；直到如今

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Until</highlight> this century, university libraries were not very price sensitive.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 直到本世纪，大学图书馆对价格还不是很敏感。

examination_example.sentence: Up <highlight>until</highlight> a few decades ago, our visions of the future were largely — though by no means uniformly — glowingly positive.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 直到几十年前，我们对未来的愿景在很大程度上——尽管并非一致——是非常乐观的。

examination_example.sentence: Children were not colour-coded at all <highlight>until</highlight> the early 20th century.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 截止到20世纪初期前的孩子们原来根本不分颜色。

word_usage.usage: until作介词，其后接名词，如：until his death；until作连词，其后接句子，如：Let's wait until the rain stops.

direction_info.description:
数据源自2016.6-2023.6年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: For the next nine days, <highlight>until</highlight> the well was capped, the well poured out more oil than all the wells in America combined.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在接下来的九天里，在油井封顶之前，油井流出的石油甚至超过了美国所有油井的总和。

examination_example.sentence: He was granted over 200 patents and continued to pioneer rocket technology <highlight>until</highlight> his death in 1945.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他获得了200多项专利，并继续开拓火箭技术，直到1945年去世。

examination_example.sentence: Growers may feel their prospects are good for an upcoming harvest, but <highlight>until</highlight> that day arrives, the outcome will always be uncertain.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 种植者可能会看好未来的收成，但在那一天到来之前，结果总是不确定的。

examination_example.sentence: I start the book and don't leave my desk <highlight>until</highlight> the first draft is finished.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我开始写这本书，并且直到第一稿完成才离开办公桌。

examination_example.sentence: A decision on the peninsula sanctuary is not expected <highlight>until</highlight> later.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 针对半岛保护区的决定预计要到晚些时候才能敲定。

examination_example.sentence: Europeans did not know of them <highlight>until</highlight> the 1500s, when Portuguese ships arrived on the coast of what is now Sierra Leone.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 直到16世纪，当葡萄牙船只抵达现在的塞拉利昂海岸时，欧洲人才知道它们。

word_usage.usage:
until常与not连用，表示“直到...才...”，注意not的翻译。
We did not notice it until yesterday.
直到昨天，我们才注意到这件事。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>

examination_example.sentence: Everything was going smoothly <highlight>until</highlight> Jeff started frying the bread.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一切都进行得很顺利，直到Jeff开始煎面包。

examination_example.sentence: These specialists could work at the office <highlight>until</highlight> ten each night.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些专家每天晚上可以在办公室工作到十点。

examination_example.sentence: I didn't think about it much <highlight>until</highlight> a morning last week when I knocked my favorite teapot off the table.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 直到上周的一个早上，我把我最喜欢的茶壶从桌子上摔下来，我才想了很久。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: till与until同义，但语气较轻；till多用于名词或较短的从句之前；放在句首时只用until，不用till。
如果要强调until引导的时间状语从句，要把not until放在一起。
